    <tags>senda api-client http rest graphql developer-tools cli git</tags>
    <summary>A fast, lightweight, git-native API client for developers.</summary>
    <description>
Senda is a desktop API client — a spiritual cousin of Bruno and Postman — where
every collection is a plain folder of YAML files. No cloud account, no
proprietary sync, no binary blobs. Open a collection, send requests, and commit
the diff.

Built with Wails (Go) and SolidJS, it ships a tiny binary with a low memory
footprint compared to Electron-based alternatives. This package installs both
the desktop app (`senda`) and the headless CLI runner (`senda-cli`).
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/gnomeria/senda/releases</releaseNotes>
  </metadata>
  <files>
    <file src="tools\**" target="tools" />
  </files>
